data.title: Los Angeles Clippers Roster
data.meta_description: Los Angeles Clippers scores, news, schedule, players, stats, rumors, depth charts and more on RealGM.com
data.text:
Kobe Brown was selected as the #30 pick in the First Round of the 2023 NBA Draft by the Los Angeles Clippers. Kobe Brown signed a multi-year contract with the Los Angeles Clippers on July 3, 2023.

Terance Mann was selected as the #18 pick in the Second Round of the 2019 NBA Draft by the Los Angeles Clippers. Terance Mann signed a multi-year contract with the Los Angeles Clippers on July 9, 2019. Terance Mann signed a multi-year extension with the Los Angeles Clippers on October 12, 2021.

Paul George was acquired in a trade by the Los Angeles Clippers from the Oklahoma City Thunder on July 10, 2019. Paul George signed a multi-year extension with the Los Angeles Clippers on December 10, 2020.

James Harden was acquired in a trade by the Los Angeles Clippers from the Philadelphia Sixers on November 1, 2023.

Bones Hyland was acquired in a trade by the Los Angeles Clippers from the Denver Nuggets on February 9, 2023.

Mason Plumlee was acquired in a trade by the Los Angeles Clippers from the Charlotte Hornets on February 9, 2023. Mason Plumlee re-signed to a contract as a free agent with the Los Angeles Clippers on July 6, 2023.

Norman Powell was acquired in a trade by the Los Angeles Clippers from the Portland Trail Blazers on February 4, 2022.

P.J. Tucker was acquired in a trade by the Los Angeles Clippers from the Philadelphia Sixers on November 1, 2023.

Ivica Zubac was acquired in a trade by the Los Angeles Clippers from the Los Angeles Lakers on February 7, 2019. Ivica Zubac re-signed to a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Los Angeles Clippers on July 10, 2019. Ivica Zubac signed a multi-year extension with the Los Angeles Clippers on June 28, 2022.

Amir Coffey signed a contract with the Los Angeles Clippers on March 26, 2022. Amir Coffey re-signed to a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Los Angeles Clippers on July 6, 2022.

Kai Jones signed a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Los Angeles Clippers on April 14, 2024.

Kawhi Leonard signed a multi-year contract with the Los Angeles Clippers on July 9, 2019. Kawhi Leonard re-signed to a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Los Angeles Clippers on August 12, 2021. Kawhi Leonard re-signed to a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Los Angeles Clippers on January 10, 2024.

Daniel Theis signed a contract as a free agent with the Los Angeles Clippers on November 17, 2023.

Russell Westbrook signed a contract with the Los Angeles Clippers on February 22, 2023. Russell Westbrook re-signed to a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Los Angeles Clippers on July 6, 2023.
